The paper is about a neural network-based adaptive sampler for motion planning in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of neural networks for adaptive sampling suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of point cloud data, which suggests that it may fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with motion planning for robots, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
